WEBVTT

00:08.083 --> 00:10.583
♪ Look at that sun
Look at that sky ♪

00:10.667 --> 00:13.000
♪ Look at my sweater vest
I look so fly ♪

00:13.083 --> 00:15.625
♪ Look at that mailbox
Look at that tree ♪

00:15.709 --> 00:18.375
♪ It's about as beautiful as it can be ♪

00:18.458 --> 00:20.959
♪ Whoa ♪

00:21.041 --> 00:23.375
♪ Today is gonna be exceptional ♪

00:23.458 --> 00:25.625
♪ Never boring even for a minute ♪

00:25.709 --> 00:28.291
♪ It's my world
And we're all livin' in it ♪

00:28.375 --> 00:31.709
♪ Whoa, whoa ♪

00:33.709 --> 00:35.542
♪ Never boring even for a minute ♪

00:35.625 --> 00:37.959
♪ It's my world
And we're all livin' in it ♪

00:46.875 --> 00:48.417
I have a secret!

00:48.500 --> 00:50.959
Milo,
that's not how secrets work.

00:51.041 --> 00:52.333
You don't just blurt it out.

00:52.500 --> 00:54.041
First, you have to hint
that you have a secret,

00:54.125 --> 00:55.709
and then you gotta wait
for someone to ask you.

00:55.792 --> 00:57.375
-So what's your secret?
-Like that.

00:57.458 --> 00:58.500
I've been taking a cooking class

00:58.583 --> 01:00.208
at the local community college.

01:00.291 --> 01:03.208
Or at least I was, till the ovens blew up.
But I learned a lot!

01:03.291 --> 01:05.458
So, I'm going to cook
dinner for you guys.

01:05.542 --> 01:07.500
Milo and open flame?

01:07.583 --> 01:09.792
Now that's a recipe for
some running and screaming.

01:10.750 --> 01:12.625
What if we just order out?

01:12.709 --> 01:15.625
They can probably deliver right to
the hospital where we'll be later.

01:15.709 --> 01:17.750
Come on, guys. I got this!

01:17.834 --> 01:20.125
Wrong chapeau, chef de cuisine.

01:20.208 --> 01:22.792
Oops. I had the silly
thing set for sleuthing.

01:23.875 --> 01:26.542
Here it goes.
First thing, open the box.

01:26.625 --> 01:27.625
[both gasping]

01:29.625 --> 01:31.542
Next, add dried noodles
to boiling water.

01:32.750 --> 01:33.625
He's boiling water!

01:33.709 --> 01:35.250
I know!

01:35.333 --> 01:36.792
Wait a second.
It looks like he knows what he's doing.

01:41.333 --> 01:43.667
You wear your backpack
while you cook?

01:43.750 --> 01:45.792
-I wear it everywhere.
-Everywhere?

01:45.875 --> 01:47.792
Well, except for backpacking.

01:47.875 --> 01:49.542
I have a different
backpack for that.

01:49.625 --> 01:52.291
So, Chef Milo,
what's your secret ingredient?

01:52.375 --> 01:54.583
It's a secret.
I don't want to ruin the surprise.

01:54.667 --> 01:56.959
What if it's not a secret and
we can prepare for it instead?

01:57.041 --> 01:58.875
Too late!
It's already ready already.

01:58.959 --> 02:00.792
Here you go! Mac and cheese!

02:01.792 --> 02:03.709
Wow, impressive!

02:03.792 --> 02:05.250
Uh-oh. Too much yeast.

02:05.333 --> 02:06.625
Yeast in mac and cheese?

02:06.709 --> 02:07.792
I guess now we know
the secret ingre...

02:07.875 --> 02:09.083
[explodes]

02:21.875 --> 02:22.875
Surprise!

02:23.917 --> 02:25.834
It's in my nose.

02:25.917 --> 02:26.917
You guys okay?

02:27.000 --> 02:28.583
Yeah,
like this is the first time

02:28.667 --> 02:30.792
we've ever been covered in
cheese and stuck to a wall.

02:30.875 --> 02:31.917
[clock ticking]

02:33.959 --> 02:35.834
Thanks for letting us borrow
a change of clothes, Milo.

02:35.917 --> 02:37.291
Is that what I look like?

02:37.375 --> 02:38.542
If you were two people

02:38.625 --> 02:39.500
and one of you was a girl.

02:39.583 --> 02:41.750
You know,
this outfit makes me feel happy.

02:41.834 --> 02:43.750
-Really?
-Yeah, there was a dollar in the pocket.

02:43.834 --> 02:45.834
Well, I think we
look like a boy band.

02:45.917 --> 02:46.750
No. We don't.

02:46.834 --> 02:49.000
We definitely don't
look like a boy band.

02:49.083 --> 02:51.542
Uh, what have you got
against boy bands?

02:51.625 --> 02:53.500
Nothing.
You know, it's just two words.

02:53.583 --> 02:55.834
Band, boy. Boy, band. Ha-ha.

02:55.917 --> 02:58.792
Who's hungry?
Come on, let's go order some pizza.

02:58.875 --> 03:01.208
Okay.

03:01.291 --> 03:02.917
Luckily, there's a place nearby.

03:03.000 --> 03:04.834
Ye Old Pizza.

03:04.917 --> 03:05.875
How does British pizza sound?

03:05.959 --> 03:07.959
A little standoffish but lovable.

03:08.041 --> 03:11.250
Never had much luck with
pizza deliveries at our house.

03:11.333 --> 03:13.834
If it shows up at all,
it's usually on fire.

03:13.917 --> 03:14.834
Let's give it a try anyway.

03:14.917 --> 03:16.458
It says it's guaranteed.

03:17.750 --> 03:19.000
[drumroll]

03:19.083 --> 03:20.667
♪ Ye Olde Pizza ♪

03:20.750 --> 03:22.667
♪ When you're tired
Of bangers and mash ♪

03:22.750 --> 03:24.000
But we've got that too!

03:24.083 --> 03:26.875
Guaranteed delivery in one
one-thousandth of a fortnight!

03:26.959 --> 03:29.625
One one-thousandth
of a fortnight?

03:29.709 --> 03:31.333
Twenty minutes and change.

03:31.417 --> 03:33.792
[man] Please wait while we connect
you to your helpful pizza squire.

03:33.875 --> 03:34.875
Allo, allo, allo.

03:34.959 --> 03:36.875
Ye Olde Pizza!

03:36.959 --> 03:39.583
Milo? I don't believe it.
Is that you?

03:39.667 --> 03:42.000
Veronica? How long have
you been a pizza squire?

03:42.083 --> 03:44.709
I haven't seen you in,
like, 300 fortnights.

03:44.959 --> 03:45.959
[Veronica] I know, right?

03:46.041 --> 03:47.375
Put the calculator down.

03:47.458 --> 03:50.041
It's been a long time.
How are you? How's Diogee?

03:50.125 --> 03:51.000
Veronica who?

03:51.083 --> 03:52.542
I thought we knew
all his friends.

03:52.625 --> 03:54.291
I thought we were
all his friends.

03:54.375 --> 03:56.500
Should I bring your favorite?
Pepperoni and sausage?

03:56.583 --> 03:58.041
Make it a large and
you can join us!

03:58.125 --> 03:59.542
And a diet soda.

03:59.625 --> 04:00.709
Hey!

04:00.792 --> 04:02.959
♪ Chop, chop,
chop Chop away at my... ♪

04:03.041 --> 04:04.041
[shrieks]

04:04.959 --> 04:06.083
What was that?

04:06.166 --> 04:07.667
Oh. I, uh, you know, chops...

04:07.750 --> 04:09.834
Maybe they have chopped salad?
[chuckles]

04:09.917 --> 04:10.875
I don't know,
do you want a chopped salad?

04:11.000 --> 04:12.166
I don't want a chopped salad.

04:12.250 --> 04:14.583
Do you want one?
But hey, Milo, huh?

04:14.667 --> 04:17.041
-Who's this Veronica person?
-Yeah.

04:17.125 --> 04:18.834
Come on, spill it, Murphy.

04:18.917 --> 04:20.834
Let's just say that with
Veronica delivering,

04:20.917 --> 04:23.792
the odds are much better that
we'll actually get the pizza.

04:23.875 --> 04:25.125
And I'll let you in
on another secret...

04:30.625 --> 04:32.041
This isn't my backpack.

04:32.125 --> 04:33.458
[both] What?

04:33.542 --> 04:34.834
[music playing]

04:39.000 --> 04:41.500
♪ I want a girl
With a suit of armor ♪

04:44.166 --> 04:47.500
♪ In chain mail,
She's a real Renaissance charmer ♪

04:47.583 --> 04:48.583
[chuckling]

04:49.917 --> 04:52.750
♪ She's not the kind of
Girl who is easily rattled ♪

04:52.834 --> 04:55.583
♪ She knows her way around
A broadsword battle ♪

04:55.667 --> 04:58.458
♪ I want a girl with
A suit of armor now ♪

04:58.542 --> 05:00.125
[Veronica] Yeah!

05:00.208 --> 05:02.667
-Wow, that's some good 3D.
-Mmm-hmm.

05:04.000 --> 05:06.166
Come on, Milo.
Who's this Veronica person?

05:06.250 --> 05:08.291
You can't just drop a bomb
like that and walk away!

05:08.375 --> 05:10.500
[Milo] You're the one who
said some secrets are cool.

05:10.583 --> 05:11.875
I bet you have some.

05:11.959 --> 05:12.959
-[in altered voice] Come on.
-[toy squeaking]

05:13.041 --> 05:14.125
Tell me your secrets!

05:14.208 --> 05:15.792
Tell them to me!

05:15.875 --> 05:18.041
Tell them to Mr. Badger!

05:18.125 --> 05:19.625
What are you doing?

05:19.709 --> 05:21.166
[in normal voice]
I'm badgering you.

05:21.250 --> 05:23.500
[in badger voice] I'm a badger!

05:23.583 --> 05:25.959
-[in normal voice] Is it workin'?
-Actually, it kind of is.

05:26.041 --> 05:27.792
I do have a secret.

05:27.875 --> 05:29.500
Okay.
This is not how I really look.

05:29.583 --> 05:30.625
You mean, you're...

05:30.709 --> 05:32.583
That's right, Zack.

05:32.667 --> 05:33.625
[in a robotic voice] I am a robot.

05:33.709 --> 05:35.625
[both screaming]

05:35.709 --> 05:37.166
I am a robot. I am a robot.

05:37.250 --> 05:38.333
-I am a robot.
-[Melissa] Zack!

05:38.375 --> 05:39.959
-[Melissa] Zack!
-Huh?

05:40.041 --> 05:42.041
-Zack, are you okay?
-Oh, right. I'm fine.

05:42.125 --> 05:43.250
So, Melissa, what's your secret?

05:43.333 --> 05:45.083
This is not how I really look.

05:45.166 --> 05:46.208
[speaking in a robotic voice]
I am a robot.

05:46.291 --> 05:47.959
[both screaming]

05:48.041 --> 05:49.208
I am a robot. I am a robot.

05:49.291 --> 05:50.917
[Zack] Melissa? Melissa!

05:51.000 --> 05:52.125
Huh? What?

05:52.208 --> 05:53.959
What do you mean,
this is not how you really look?

05:55.041 --> 05:56.208
My two front teeth are fake.

05:56.291 --> 05:57.709
Caught a pop fly with my face.

05:58.792 --> 05:59.834
[screams]

06:00.083 --> 06:01.625
[thuds]

06:05.709 --> 06:07.709
Okay, everyone,
we've got an oil spill here.

06:07.792 --> 06:09.333
Highly flammable. Stay back.

06:09.417 --> 06:11.125
Hey, mister, that's not oil.

06:11.208 --> 06:13.041
-That's molasses!
-Really?

06:13.750 --> 06:14.750
Okay then.

06:16.125 --> 06:17.250
Ah!

06:19.750 --> 06:21.750
Why didn't you tell me
molasses was flammable?

06:21.834 --> 06:22.834
I'm four.

06:26.917 --> 06:30.208
♪ Chop, chop,
chop Chop away at my heart ♪

06:30.291 --> 06:31.291
[barking]

06:32.125 --> 06:33.125
Whoa! Timber!

06:35.750 --> 06:37.041
-[barking]
-Diogee!

06:37.125 --> 06:38.875
You're a lot bigger
than I remember!

06:38.959 --> 06:41.834
Here you go.
Let's take you home.

06:41.917 --> 06:43.375
This is the worst
assignment yet.

06:43.458 --> 06:46.250
Stopping pistachios from
leaking out of a silo.

06:46.333 --> 06:47.875
Yeah, but there are perks.
Check it out.

06:49.792 --> 06:51.250
Stop that,
you're making it worse!

06:52.125 --> 06:53.166
See?

06:53.250 --> 06:54.250
[motorcycle approaching]

06:55.959 --> 06:58.250
Wanna give me a hand here?
At least a finger?

06:58.333 --> 07:00.166
Fine. Like this?

07:00.250 --> 07:01.333
[both] Whoa!

07:03.333 --> 07:04.834
[Veronica] Hold on, Diogee!

07:04.917 --> 07:05.834
Whoa!

07:08.250 --> 07:09.959
Well,
Murphy's Law is in full force.

07:10.041 --> 07:11.333
What we need now is some power.

07:12.792 --> 07:14.083
We're gonna have to improvise.

07:14.166 --> 07:16.250
Mints and diet soda.

07:19.792 --> 07:21.000
Take cover, boy.

07:22.375 --> 07:23.667
Hold on to your tail!

07:27.166 --> 07:30.291
-Guys, she's getting close. I can feel it.
-[Veronica] Milo!

07:30.375 --> 07:31.750
I'm coming in hot!

07:31.834 --> 07:33.083
Battle stations, everyone!

07:33.166 --> 07:34.875
Melissa, fire extinguisher.

07:34.959 --> 07:36.834
Zack, trampoline! Ready?

07:36.917 --> 07:37.917
-Ready.
-Ready.

07:41.542 --> 07:43.000
Whoa!

07:43.375 --> 07:45.166
[grunts]

07:49.375 --> 07:51.166
One one-thousandth
of a fortnight.

07:51.291 --> 07:52.750
And it's not even on fire.

07:52.834 --> 07:54.333
Whoop. Spoke too soon.

07:56.458 --> 07:58.000
But, none the worse for wear.

07:58.083 --> 08:00.125
Everybody, this is Veronica.

08:00.208 --> 08:02.625
Veronica, these are my
other two friends.

08:02.709 --> 08:03.792
Hello!

08:03.875 --> 08:05.792
Okay, so how do you
guys know each other?

08:05.875 --> 08:08.041
Veronica was my last babysitter.

08:08.125 --> 08:09.750
Last babysitter standing.

08:09.834 --> 08:11.125
[both] Oh.

08:11.208 --> 08:12.333
She was the only
one smart enough,

08:12.417 --> 08:14.083
and resourceful
enough for the job.

08:14.166 --> 08:15.709
She had a backpack that
just happened to have

08:15.792 --> 08:19.125
exactly what we needed
to fix any disaster.

08:19.208 --> 08:21.250
Murphy's Law is strong,
but she was stronger...

08:22.834 --> 08:24.000
Because of that backpack.

08:24.083 --> 08:25.792
And that's her backpack!

08:25.875 --> 08:27.208
-That's right.
-He earned it.

08:27.291 --> 08:29.000
I better go back
and get that drink.

08:29.083 --> 08:30.000
I had to use your diet soda

08:30.083 --> 08:32.333
and some mints to
improvise an afterburner.

08:32.417 --> 08:34.250
Don't make that trip
again on my account.

08:34.333 --> 08:35.750
Oh, no, it's my pleasure.

08:35.834 --> 08:38.041
I was a huge fan
of the Lumberzacks!

08:38.125 --> 08:40.000
Gotta go! Chop, chop, chop!

08:40.083 --> 08:41.083
[kissing]

08:41.917 --> 08:43.250
[whistling]

08:43.333 --> 08:45.333
I'll be back with
the soda in a few!

08:48.917 --> 08:50.250
Soooo...

08:50.333 --> 08:52.000
-Pizza?
-I don't get it.

08:52.083 --> 08:53.291
How did she know your name?

08:53.375 --> 08:55.166
And what the heck
is a Lumberzack?

08:55.250 --> 08:57.166
[chuckles] I guess we'll never know.

08:57.250 --> 08:58.166
Unless we just look up

08:58.250 --> 09:01.125
"Lumberzacks,
Chop Chop Chop" on the Internet.

09:01.208 --> 09:02.291
Oh, no.

09:02.375 --> 09:04.375
Oh, this is gonna be good!

09:04.458 --> 09:06.041
-[music playing]
-[tree crashing]

09:07.458 --> 09:09.500
♪ I know you're pining ♪

09:09.583 --> 09:13.291
♪ But every cloud has
Got a silver lining ♪

09:13.375 --> 09:16.750
♪ The leaves have parted
Now the sun is shining ♪

09:16.834 --> 09:19.208
♪ And you're in my arms ♪

09:19.291 --> 09:22.500
♪ So the planets are aligning ♪

09:22.583 --> 09:24.208
♪ My heart is strong ♪

09:24.625 --> 09:25.792
♪ Like a tree ♪

09:26.291 --> 09:28.417
♪ And you belong ♪

09:28.500 --> 09:30.291
♪ Baby, you belong to me ♪

09:30.375 --> 09:31.875
♪ Without you ♪

09:31.959 --> 09:34.041
♪ I'm tied to the ground ♪

09:34.125 --> 09:35.333
♪ And if I fall ♪

09:35.417 --> 09:38.208
♪ Do I even make a sound? ♪

09:38.291 --> 09:42.291
♪ Chop, chop,
Chop Chop away at my heart ♪

09:42.375 --> 09:44.333
-♪ I can feel it falling ♪
-Timber!

09:44.417 --> 09:46.041
♪ And now we'll never part ♪

09:46.125 --> 09:47.417
♪ I know you ♪

09:47.500 --> 09:49.417
♪ You've been there from the start ♪

09:49.500 --> 09:51.166
♪ So, baby Chop, chop, chop ♪

09:51.250 --> 09:53.417
♪ Chop away at my heart ♪

09:53.500 --> 09:57.000
[vocalizing]

10:08.583 --> 10:12.583
♪ Chop, chop,
Chop Chop away at my heart ♪

10:12.667 --> 10:14.250
He's so sensitive.

10:14.333 --> 10:15.417
I know, right?

10:15.500 --> 10:17.250
Please turn it off.

10:17.333 --> 10:18.250
I will give you this dollar

10:18.333 --> 10:19.792
I found in your pocket.

10:19.875 --> 10:21.583
Oh, you can keep that.

10:21.667 --> 10:23.834
♪ Chop away at my heart ♪

10:23.917 --> 10:27.458
♪ Chop, chop, chop
Chop away at my heart ♪

10:27.542 --> 10:29.625
-♪ I can feel it falling ♪
-Timber!

10:29.709 --> 10:31.250
♪ And now we'll never part ♪

10:31.333 --> 10:32.792
♪ I know you ♪

10:32.875 --> 10:34.917
♪ You've been there from the start ♪

10:35.000 --> 10:36.375
♪ So, baby
Chop, chop, chop ♪

10:36.458 --> 10:39.291
♪ Chop away at my heart ♪

10:39.375 --> 10:42.291
You were in a
lumberjack-themed boy band.

10:42.375 --> 10:44.041
We were regionally famous.

10:44.125 --> 10:46.500
The lumberjack thing
was not my idea.

10:46.583 --> 10:49.250
My mom had a bunch of flannel and...
[sighs]

10:49.333 --> 10:50.917
But you were in a band!

10:51.000 --> 10:52.458
It's really cool, Zack.

10:52.542 --> 10:54.291
Hey! We should start a band!

10:54.375 --> 10:55.417
I can play the bass.

10:55.500 --> 10:56.500
That's cool.

10:56.583 --> 10:58.208
And I've got an accordion!

10:58.291 --> 11:01.542
Potentially cool,
in a hipster kind of way.

11:01.625 --> 11:03.417
[Diogee barking]

11:03.500 --> 11:06.500
-And now we have to order another pizza.
-[barking]

11:06.583 --> 11:08.667
♪ It's my world and
we're all livin' in it ♪
